title: Grateful Dead Live at The Spectrum on 1980-08-30
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) > Korg MR-1000 (1-bit/5.6MHz) > Audiogate (1-bit/5.6MHz > 16-bit/44.1KHz) > cdwav (edits)
description:
Set 1

Feel Like A Stranger, Peggy-O, Cassidy, Friend Of The Devil, Minglewood Blues, Cold Rain & Snow-> Looks Like Rain, Easy To Love You, Althea, Jack Straw

Set 2

Scarlet Begonias-> Fire On The Mountain, CC Rider-> Ramble On Rose, Estimated Prophet-> Eyes Of The World-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Black Peter-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Good Sounding Aud Starts out a little thin, but I think thats just Healy working it out. The Spectum was bathed in Summer light streaming through the section portals for most of the 1st Set, and the band obviously responded to it being my B-Day  and 2nd show ever. This is probable the best you could ask for for a young Dead Head to cut their teeth on, Philly, August, 1980, Mickey the Sorcerer. A great set list. This aud is pretty good and definitly worth a download
